article.headline: Stony Brook 73, New Hampshire 64
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. (AP) -- Antwan Hardy scored 15 points to lead Stony Brook to a 73-64 victory over New Hampshire on Sunday. Bobby Santiago had 12 points, including a 3-pointer in the decisive 9-0 run that gave the Seawolves (6-7, 1-3 America East) a 65-56 lead. Mike Christensen and Blagov Janev each had 14 points for the Wildcats (5-8, 1-3). Janev made two free throws with 7:46 left to tie the game at 56. Hendrik Feist and Santiago had 3s in the run that gave Stony Brook the lead for good. Jairus McCollum had 10 points and nine rebounds for the Seawolves, while Cori Spencer had 10 points and eight rebounds.
